UpdateUser(string,string,bytes32,uint256.details: Adds a new user or updates an existing user's data IN THIS CONTRACT. This is the function your TEE calls to migrate data or update it. It can only be called by the contract owner.

params._username: The username that acts as the key in the mapping.

constructor.details: The constructor is called by the ReputationFactory.

params._creator: The TEE address that will own this new Reputation.
params._referrerReputation: The address of the old contract to chain lookups to.

getUserData(string).details: Custom getter to perform a single-level lookup for user data. It first checks this contract, then falls back to the immediate referrer. If data is found in referrer, it copies it to this contract for future lookups.

returns._0: The UserData struct for the user.
